data.text: I get the sense that Chaeyeon will be this season's Samuel, though, and it makes me sad for her.
I also kinda like Miho's vocals. She's not main vocal material, but I like her tone and think she adds a lot to songs she sings. I thought Miu suited this song and did well on stage, too.

Moe has such a bright and fun personality and when that's showcased on stage it's very enjoyable to watch her. I know she has her technical issues, but I think she adds a lot of energy and happiness to the performances she's in. Personal opinion tho

I think 1000% was my favorite stage. I can't really say why, but it made me the happiest when I was watching it. Maybe it's because Moe was practically glowing and I was just so happy to see her look happy again.
I was so impressed with Haeyoon in Let's Meet Again! I love her voice and I want her to be in the final 12 so bad! I also thought Miyu did very well in this song.

Rollin' Rollin' was undoubtedly the most fun stage. I thought Hitomi did very well and I was impressed with Miru's ability to pull off this concept when before she had always done more mature/sexy concepts. She's more well-rounded that I thought.
I think I Wish was the most polished and well-rounded group. All of the members did well. They all have good vocals and suited the song well.
I Am was also underwhelming, which is odd because all of the trainees in it are super talented. But it just felt lackluster and I'm not sure why?
Eunbi was a standout as the main vocal. She really suited the song in both her image and her vocals. She was a perfect fit for the chorus. I was also impressed with Sihyun's stage presence.
